 to range from  to  billion dollars frazier said the case was the most significant challenge hed ever faced he chose to fight all cases in court rather than settle them all quickly the remaining cases were settled in  for  billion in  frazier was promoted to executive vice president in addition to his role as general counsel he led the companys largest group human health from  until he was named president of merck  co in april  on january   he became ceo and a member of the companys board of directors replacing former merck  co ceo richard clark frazier was the first africanamerican to lead a major pharmaceutical company as ceo frazier has directed the company to take financial risks in developing new treatments in  he prioritized research funding over meeting the years earnings target he has placed special emphasis on improving treatments for alzheimers disease fraziers father died from alzheimers frazier has said he is also motivated at merck  co by a desire to improve the lives of people in developing countries frazier received a total compensation of  in  according to the annual collaborative report from equilar and the new york times frazier ranked th in the may  list of  highestpaid ceos of large publicly traded companies and seventh in the list of biopharmaceutical executives with the highest total compensation in july  frazier sold  shares of the firms stock the stock was sold at an average price of  other workedit on november   as a member of the penn state board of trustees the board selected frazier as chairman of a commission empaneled to investigate a child sex abuse scandal involving former assistant football coach jerry sandusky and allegations of a cover up by university officials the commission retained the private law firm freeh sporkin  sullivan as special investigative counsel who then hired pepper hamilton legal counsel for merck  co the report costing the university  million was accepted and used as the basis for the ncaa sanctions against penn state frazier was criticized by attorney william cluck and other penn state alumni for his role in the penn state board of trustees handling of the jerry sandusky scandal particularly its decision to fire head football coach joe paterno frazier responded to mr cluck with a tirade saying to the lightskinned mr cluck if you cared about that you are one of the few people in this country that looks like you who actually believes the oj simpson not guilty verdict was correct mr frazier issued a minimal apology shortly after the event and then with the benefit of counsel from merck  co a more thorough apology for the inappropriate outburst frazier is a member of the american law institute and serves on its council in may  he delivered the keynote speech at the ali annual dinner offering some reflections on my experiences as a lawyer in private and inhouse practice and from my current vantage point as ceo of a global healthcare company on the importance of our legal system and lawyers for business for society and for all of our people see alsoedit raymond gilmartin referencesedit  a b c d e rice lewis i summer  a dose of optimism harvard law bulletin   a b c chen vivia february   master of the game the minority law journal registration required help   a b c d e f g hepp christopher k december   new merck ceo kenneth c frazier has philadelphia roots philadelphia inquirer   a b c d e merck new ceo frazier vows innovation wider markets bloomberg november     a b president obama announces more key administration posts the white house september     a b rogers lisa march   cochran continues to inspire gadsden times p b   a b c randall tom march   mercks risky bet on research bloomberg businessweek   a b c d pierson ransdell krauskopf lewis november   merck elevates frazier to succeed clark as ceo reuters   koppel nathan november   another lawyer done good merck names frazier ceo wall street journal  law blog   a b c johnson linda a march   ceo risks key for merck to succeed hel