 that is open honest and transparent ken frazier chairman and ceo merck our executive committee manages the business of merck these top leaders representing diverse areas of the company meet regularly to review progress against our company goals executive committee our chairman and ceo ken frazier is accountable to the merck board of directors learn more about our board members including committee charters and assignments board members corporate governance certificate of incorporation bylaws policies of the board  a statement of mercks corporate governance guidelines board committee charters committee assignments corporate responsibility corporate governance code of conductour values and standards the merck code of conduct reflects our corporate values and guides our daytoday decision making our code of conduct shareholder communications with the board learn more copyright   merck sharp  dohme corp a subsidiary of merck  co inc all rights reserved forwardlooking statement privacy terms of use site map ×close forwardlooking statement forwardlooking statement of merck  co inc kenilworth nj usa this website of merck  co inc kenilworth nj usa the “company” includes “forwardlooking statements” within the meaning of the safe harbor provisions of the united states private securities litigation reform act of  these statements are based upon the current beliefs and expectations of the company’s management and are subject to significant risks and uncertainties there can be no guarantees with respect to pipeline products that the products will receive the necessary regulatory approvals or that they will prove to be commercially successful if underlying assumptions prove inaccurate or risks or uncertainties materialize actual results may differ materially from those set forth in the forwardlooking statements risks and uncertainties include but are not limited to general industry conditions and competition general economic factors including interest rate and currency exchange ra