 the chairman and ceo of the pharmaceutical company merck  co known as msd outside of north america after joining merck  co as general counsel he directed the companys defense against litigation over the antiinflammatory drug vioxx frazier is the second africanamerican to lead a major pharmaceutical company contents  early life  career  drinker biddle  merck  co  other work  see also  references early lifeedit kenneth frazier was born on december   in north philadelphia his father otis was a janitor frazier has said thurgood marshall was one of his heroes growing up fraziers mother died when he was twelve years old he attended northeast high school after graduating at age  he entered pennsylvania state university to make extra money in college he raised tadpoles and newts and sold them to local stores after earning his ba from penn state frazier enrolled at harvard university to study law he graduated in  with a jd careeredit drinker biddleedit frazier started his law career at drinker biddle  reath after graduating from harvard in philadelphia in  esther lardent head of the death penalty representation project asked frazier to defend death row inmate james willie bo cochran cochran had been arrested and accused of murdering an assistant manager at a birmingham grocery store in  frazier then a partner at drinker biddle and two colleagues took the case in  after  years on death row the th united states courts of appeals overturned cochrans conviction in  cochran was retried and found not guilty frazier continued to represent him after leaving drinker biddle during fraziers law career he also took four summer sabbaticals to teach trial advocacy in south africa merck  coedit as a lawyer at drinker biddle one of fraziers clients was merck  co the secondlargest drug company in the united states in  he joined merck  cos public affairs division as general counsel frazier was named senior general counsel in  as general counsel he was credited with overseeing the companys defense against claims that the antiinflammatory drug vioxx had caused heart attacks and strokes analysts at the time estimated merck  cos liability to range from  to  billion dollars frazier said the case was the most significant challenge hed ever faced he chose to fight all cases in court rather than settle them all quickly the remaining cases were settled in  for  billion in  frazier was promoted to executive vice president in addition to his role as general counsel he led the companys largest group human health from  until he was named president of merck  co in april  on january   he became ceo and a member of the companys board of directors replacing former merck  co ceo richard clark frazier was the first africanamerican to lead a major pharmaceutical company as ceo frazier has directed the company to take financial risks in developing new treatments in  he prioritized research funding over meeting the years earnings target he has placed special emphasis on improving treatments for alzheimers disease fraziers father died from alzheimers frazier has said he is also motivated at merck  co by a desire to improve the lives of people in developing countries frazier received a total compensation of  in  according to the annual collaborative report from equilar and the new york times frazier ranked th in the may  list of  highestpaid ceos of large publicly traded companies and seventh in the list of biopharmaceutical executives with the highest total compensation in july  frazier sold  shares of the firms stock the stock was sold at an average price of  other workedit on november   as a member of the penn state board of trustees the board selected frazier as chairman of a commission empaneled to investigate a child sex abuse scandal involving former assistant football coach jerry sandusky and allegations of a cover up by university officials the commission retained the private law firm freeh sporkin  sullivan as special investigative counsel who then hired pepper hamilton legal counsel for merck  co the report costing the university  million was accepted and used as the basis for the ncaa sanctions against penn state frazier was criticized by attorney william cluck and other penn state alumni for his role in the penn state board of trustees handling of the jerry sandusky scandal particularly its decision to fire head football coach joe paterno frazier responded to mr cluck with a tirade saying to the lightskinned mr cluck if you cared about that you are one of the few people in this country that looks like you who actually believes the oj simpson not guilty verdict was correct mr frazier issued a minimal apology shortly after the event and then with the benefit of counsel from merck  co a more thorough apology for the inappropriate outburst frazier is a member of the american law institute and serves on its council in may  he delivered the keynote speech at the ali annual dinner offering some reflections on my experiences as a lawyer in private and inhouse practice and from my current vantage point as ceo of a global healthcare company on the importance of our legal system and lawyers for business for society and for all of our people see alsoedit raymond gilmartin referencesedit  a b c d e rice lewis i summer  a dose of optimism harvard law bulletin   a b c chen vivia february   master of the game the minority law journal registration required help   a b c d e f g hepp christopher k december   new merck ceo kenneth c frazier has philadelphia roots philadelphia inquirer   a b c d e merck new ceo frazier vows innovation wider markets bloomberg november     a b president obama announces more key administration posts the white house september     a b rogers lisa march   cochran continues to inspire gadsden times p b   a b c randall tom march   mercks risky bet on research bloomberg businessweek   a b c d pierson ransdell krauskopf lewis november   merck elevates frazier to succeed clark as ceo reuters   koppel nathan november   ano